  "detailedRequirements": "<div class=\"previewMask\">\n<p><span>We&#39;ve been building a mobile magazine application over these past few months. It grabs content from all over the internet, aggregates it together, and displays it in a nice HTML5 front end.</span></p>\n\n<p><span>Previously, we have updated the app to show the images grabbed from external services instead of showing placehoder images (this changes are already in github). </span></p>\n\n<p><span>But there is a problem with this change.</span> a<span>s the grabbed images are in different width and height, there are stretch problems. </span></p>\n\n<p><span>In order to </span>fix this problem, we&#39;d like to dynamically check the image size and use proper CSS to control it been displayed in the box.<br />\nLet&#39;s say the box is 200px * 200px (the box size for different sections are different),<br />\n1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;if the image size is fit in, we can directly show it without stretch,<br />\n2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;if the image size has larger width, then we have to use CSS like {width: 100%; height: auto} in order to show proper aspect ratio.<br />\n3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;if the image size has larger height, then we have to use CSS like {width: auto; height: 100%} in order to show proper aspect ratio.<br />\n4.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;if the image size has larger width and height, then we have to dynamically determine to use 2 or 3 approach above.</p>\n\n<p><span>Reference <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/9994493/scale-image-to-fit-a-bounding-box-css-only/9994936#9994936\">link</a> for the above approach.&nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p>Your solution should also consider that cases for missing image.</p>\n\n<p><span>You can get the latest code from our <a href=\"https://github.com/cloudspokes/Mnemosyne-Mobile-Magazine\">Github repo.</a> If you do not have access, post the forums and we will get you in. The latest version of the REST API and aggregator code are also there, if you want to setup your own environment.</span></p>\n\n<p>a copy of the latest source code will also be attached in forum.</p>\n\n<p><span>For this challenge, you can use our backend services in our demo server (</span>54.87.113.189<span>).</span></p>\n\n<p>The general idea is to make the screen looks pretty and professional, any other improvement are also wellcom.</p>\n\n<p>Please test the app in iPad (Potrait and landscape mode) and iPhone (Potrait mode).</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n",
